<section id="key-insights" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="key-insights">Key Insights</h2>
<p>The P&amp;C Severity CPI has consistently outpaced general CPI-U inflation since 2010, with notable acceleration during:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li><strong>2021-2022</strong>: Supply chain disruptions drove auto parts and repair costs sharply higher</li>
<li><strong>2023-2024</strong>: Medical inflation and construction labor costs remained elevated</li>
<li><strong>Current</strong>: The gap between P&amp;C severity inflation and CPI-U remains significant</li>
</ol>
</section>
<section id="what-this-index-doesnt-capture" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="what-this-index-doesnt-capture">What This Index Doesn’t Capture</h2>
<p>Important caveats:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Social inflation</strong> and litigation trends</li>
<li><strong>Regulatory changes</strong> or fee schedule modifications</li>
<li><strong>Claim frequency</strong> shifts</li>
<li><strong>Regional variation</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>Always supplement with loss development analysis and market-specific data.</p>
</section>
